---
import ArticleLayout from '../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: "pricing", label: "Pricing Comparison" },
  { id: "features", label: "Feature Comparison" },
  { id: "pricebook", label: "Pricebook & Sales" },
  { id: "marketing", label: "Marketing Tools" },
  { id: "onboarding", label: "Onboarding & Setup" },
  { id: "who-fits", label: "Who Each Fits" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Verdict" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQ" }
];
const faqItems = [
  { q: "Is ServiceTitan worth the extra cost over Housecall Pro?", a: "For companies with 10+ technicians and $3M+ revenue, ServiceTitan's pricebook and marketing attribution typically generate enough additional revenue to justify the 5-10x price difference. For teams under 10 techs, Housecall Pro delivers 80% of the functionality at 20% of the cost." },
  { q: "Can I switch from Housecall Pro to ServiceTitan?", a: "Yes, but expect a 6-16 week implementation process and $5,000-$50,000 in setup costs. ServiceTitan offers migration support. Most companies run both platforms in parallel for 4-8 weeks during the transition." },
  { q: "Can I switch from ServiceTitan to Housecall Pro?", a: "Yes. Export your data from ServiceTitan (CSV) and import into Housecall Pro. The reverse migration is faster (days, not weeks) because Housecall Pro has no formal implementation process. Watch out for ServiceTitan early termination fees." },
  { q: "Which is better for a 5-technician HVAC company?", a: "Housecall Pro. At $149/month vs $1,225-$1,725/month for ServiceTitan, the cost difference is $12,000-$18,000/year. A 5-tech team rarely uses the enterprise features that justify ServiceTitan's price." },
  { q: "Which has better reporting?", a: "ServiceTitan. Its reporting dashboards cover technician performance, revenue by department, marketing ROI, and custom KPIs. Housecall Pro's reporting is adequate for small businesses but larger operations often outgrow it." }
];
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="ServiceTitan vs Housecall Pro for HVAC (2026): When to Pay 10x More — HVAC Software Hub"
  description="ServiceTitan costs $1,225-$1,725/month for 5 techs. Housecall Pro costs $149. We compare features, pricing, and which platform fits different HVAC team sizes."
  canonicalPath="/hvac/crm/servicetitan-vs-housecall-pro"
  category="Comparisons"
  publishDate="2026-04-06"
  readTime="12 min read"
  intent="BOFU"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  faqItems={faqItems}
>
<div class="container py-8">
  <div class="flex gap-12">
    <article class="flex-1 min-w-0 max-w-3xl">

      <div class="prose mt-8">
        <p>ServiceTitan and Housecall Pro serve the same industry but target different stages of growth. ServiceTitan is built for large, established HVAC operations. Housecall Pro is built for small to mid-size teams getting organized. The pricing gap between them is enormous, so the question is not "which is better" but "which one fits your current business."</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose" id="pricing">
        <h2>Pricing: The Core Difference</h2>
      </div>
      <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin: 16px 0; font-size: 14px;">
        <thead>
          <tr style="background:#1B4F72; color:white;">
            <th style="padding:10px; text-align:left;"></th>
            <th style="padding:10px;">ServiceTitan</th>
            <th style="padding:10px;">Housecall Pro</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">Pricing model</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Per technician</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Flat monthly tiers</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">5-tech monthly cost</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$1,225-$1,725</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$149-$249</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">10-tech monthly cost</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$2,450-$3,450</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$329-$399</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">Annual cost (10 techs)</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$29,400-$41,400</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$3,948-$4,788</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">Implementation fee</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$5,000-$50,000</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">$0</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">Contract</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">12+ months (often multi-year)</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Month-to-month</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">Free trial</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">No</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">14 days, no credit card</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px; font-weight:600;">Time to go live</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">6-16 weeks</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">1-3 days</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>A 10-technician HVAC company saves <strong>$25,000-$37,000 per year</strong> by choosing Housecall Pro over ServiceTitan. The question is whether ServiceTitan's additional features generate enough revenue to cover that gap.</p>
        <p>For detailed pricing breakdowns, see <a href="/hvac/pricing/servicetitan-pricing">ServiceTitan Pricing 2026</a> and <a href="/hvac/pricing/housecall-pro-pricing">Housecall Pro Pricing 2026</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose" id="features">
        <h2>Feature Comparison</h2>
      </div>
      <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin: 16px 0; font-size: 14px;">
        <thead>
          <tr style="background:#1B4F72; color:white;">
            <th style="padding:10px; text-align:left;">Feature</th>
            <th style="padding:10px;">ServiceTitan</th>
            <th style="padding:10px;">Housecall Pro</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px;">Scheduling & dispatch</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Advanced (capacity planning, zone-based)</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Standard (drag-and-drop, GPS)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Flat-rate pricebook</td>
