          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Reporting</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Enterprise-grade (custom KPI dashboards, department revenue)</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Adequate for small teams</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px;">Online booking</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Available</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Built-in from Basic plan</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Review management</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Available</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Built-in from Basic plan</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px;">Mobile app</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">iPad required</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">iOS and Android</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px;">QuickBooks integration</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">All plans</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Essentials+ ($149/mo)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding:10px;">Memberships/service plans</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Built-in</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Add-on</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Call tracking</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">Phones Pro (add-on)</td>
            <td style="padding:10px;">VoIP add-on</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="prose" id="pricebook">
        <h2>Pricebook and Sales Presentation</h2>
        <p>This is ServiceTitan's biggest competitive advantage. The Good-Better-Best pricebook presentation lets technicians show homeowners three options on an iPad. Users consistently report a <strong>15-25% increase in average ticket size</strong> after implementing this feature.</p>
        <p>For a 10-tech HVAC company running $3M in revenue, a 15% ticket increase adds $450,000 in annual revenue. That makes ServiceTitan's $30,000-$40,000 annual cost look like a 10:1 return.</p>
        <p>Housecall Pro has a Sales Proposals add-on ($40/month) that achieves a similar result but with less polish and automation. It works, but it is not at ServiceTitan's level.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose" id="marketing">
        <h2>Marketing Attribution</h2>
        <p>ServiceTitan's Marketing Pro is the other feature that justifies the premium. It connects your ad spend (Google Ads, LSA, direct mail, radio) to actual booked revenue, showing you exactly which campaigns generate jobs and which ones waste money.</p>
        <p>At $2,000+/month, Marketing Pro is expensive. But for companies spending $5,000-$20,000/month on advertising, knowing which half of the budget is wasted pays for the tool many times over.</p>
        <p>Housecall Pro tracks lead sources at a basic level (which marketing channel the customer came from) but cannot tie ad spend to revenue the way ServiceTitan does.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose" id="onboarding">
        <h2>Onboarding and Time to Value</h2>
        <p><strong>Housecall Pro:</strong> Sign up, start the 14-day free trial, import your customer list, and you are running jobs within 1-3 days. There is no formal implementation. The learning curve is short.</p>
        <p><strong>ServiceTitan:</strong> 6-16 weeks from contract signing to go-live. The implementation includes pricebook configuration, data migration, CSR training, dispatcher training, and technician training. You will run both your old system and ServiceTitan in parallel for 4-8 weeks. Most companies report that it takes 3-6 months to fully realize the platform's value.</p>
        <p>If you need to be operational by next week, Housecall Pro is the only option. If you can invest 3-6 months in a platform transition, ServiceTitan's long-term payoff is typically worth the slow start.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose" id="who-fits">
        <h2>Who Each Platform Fits</h2>
        <h3>Choose Housecall Pro if:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Your team has fewer than 10 technicians</li>
          <li>Annual revenue is under $3M</li>
          <li>You need to be operational quickly (days, not months)</li>
          <li>Budget flexibility matters (month-to-month, no contracts)</li>
          <li>You do not have dedicated office staff to manage complex software</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Choose ServiceTitan if:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Your team has 10+ technicians with dedicated dispatch and office staff</li>
          <li>Annual revenue exceeds $3M (ideally $5M+)</li>
          <li>You use flat-rate pricing and want Good-Better-Best pricebook automation</li>
          <li>You spend $5,000+/month on marketing and need attribution data</li>
          <li>You can invest in a 3-6 month implementation without disrupting operations</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="prose" id="verdict">
        <h2>Verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>Housecall Pro is the right choice for 80% of HVAC companies.</strong> It covers scheduling, dispatching, invoicing, customer communication, and review management at a price that makes sense for small to mid-size teams.</p>
        <p><strong>ServiceTitan is the right choice for the other 20%.</strong> Large, established operations with the team, budget, and operational maturity to maximize the pricebook, marketing attribution, and enterprise reporting features.</p>
        <p>The mistake most contractors make: buying ServiceTitan too early. Start with Housecall Pro (or <a href="/hvac/pricing/jobber-pricing">Jobber</a>), grow to 10+ techs, then evaluate ServiceTitan when the ROI math works.</p>

